<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/prefs_main_template/macros/master">

  <metal:main metal:fill-slot="prefs_configlet_main" i18n:domain="quintagroup.analytics">
    <body>
        <div id="wrapper">
            <h1>Content ownership by state</h1>
            <ul class="formTabs" id="navigation">
                <li class="formTab"><a class="selected" href="@@qa_overview">Overview</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@ownership_by_type">Ownership by type</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@ownership_by_state">Ownership by state</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@type_by_state">Types by state</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@legacy_portlets">Legacy portlets</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@properties_stats">Properties stats</a></li>
                <li class="formTab"><a href="@@portlets_stats">Portlets stats</a></li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Welcome to Quintagroup Analytics Tool</h2>
            <p>This control panel configlet provides statistic information about your Plone site.
               Every above tab displays information about site content, properties and portlets.
               You can see how many content objects are on you site, who are content owners,
               what are content workflow states, etc. You can simply find all portlets that are
               assigned on your site and even edit them. You can also export this information into .csv file.
               This information can be very helpful: it allows you to see your site's
               overall content from different perspectives. This information can be very useful while
               migrating your site into newer Plone version, or into another CMS.
            </p>
            <dl>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@ownership_by_type">Ownership by type</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>This tab gives you information about content owners.</dd>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@ownership_by_state">Ownership by state</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>Here you can see information about content and it workflow states.
                  You can see how many content object are published and by whom.</dd>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@type_by_state">Types by state</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>This view provides information about content types and their workflow states.</dd>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@legacy_portlets">Legacy portlets</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>On this tab you can see legacy portlets information and where they are assigned.</dd>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@properties_stats">Properties stats</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>On this tab you can see certain property values for all site objects.</dd>
              <dt>
                <a href="@@portlets_stats">Portlets stats</a>
              </dt>
              <dd>On this tab you can see portlets information and where they are assigned.</dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
    </body>
  </metal:main>
</html>
